<!-- 0: STRATEGIC QUESTIONS -->
<div class="section" id="q0">
  <div class="section-eyebrow"><div class="section-num">0</div><div class="section-label">Foundation</div></div>
  <h2>The Four Strategic Questions</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">Alchemy Wealth Builders operates three interconnected business lines: Investment Syndication & Fund Management, Real Estate Brokerage (residential, commercial, business buy/sell), and Commercial Real Estate (CRE) — including hotels, multifamily, and assisted living. Every social media decision must serve all three.</p>
  <div class="answer-box">
    <div class="answer-q">Why are we posting? — Goals</div>
    <div class="answer-a">To position Alchemy Wealth Builders as the premier authority across three verticals: (1) passive real estate investing and syndication for accredited investors, (2) full-service brokerage for buyers, sellers, and business owners, and (3) commercial real estate including hotels, multifamily, and assisted living. Every post drives toward three actions: Investor Club sign-ups, brokerage inquiry form submissions, or discovery call bookings.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="answer-box">
    <div class="answer-q">Who are we speaking to? — Audience</div>
    <div class="answer-a">Four personas: The Aspiring Passive Investor (W2 professionals seeking financial freedom through syndication), The Accredited Diversifier (high-net-worth individuals seeking CRE exposure), The Property Buyer/Seller (residential and commercial clients needing brokerage services), and The Business Owner (entrepreneurs looking to buy or sell a business through Alchemy's brokerage division).</div>
  </div>
  <div class="answer-box">
    <div class="answer-q">What will we post? — Content Pillars & Formats</div>
    <div class="answer-a">Seven content pillars covering: Real Estate Education, Deal Spotlight (syndication & CRE), Brokerage Showcase (listings, buyer/seller tips, business transactions), Financial Freedom Lifestyle, Market Insights, Behind the Brand (Ankit Desai's story and team), and Social Proof & Community. Delivered through carousels, Reels, YouTube deep-dives, thought leadership articles, listing showcases, and live Q&As.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="answer-box">
    <div class="answer-q">Where and when will we post? — Platforms & Schedule</div>
    <div class="answer-a">Primary: LinkedIn (investor and professional audience, M/W/F) and Instagram (brokerage listings, brand awareness, daily). Secondary: YouTube (weekly long-form), Facebook (community group + local brokerage reach, 3x/week), TikTok (reach and awareness, 5x/week). Peak windows: 7–9 AM and 6–8 PM US Eastern/Pacific time.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="answer-box" style="margin-bottom:0;">
    <div class="answer-q">How will we measure success? — KPIs & Reporting</div>
    <div class="answer-a">Three conversion tracks: (1) Investor Club sign-ups (target 50/month by Month 6), (2) Brokerage inquiry form submissions (target 20/month by Month 4), and (3) Discovery call bookings (target 30/month by Month 9). Supporting metrics: follower growth (15% MoM), engagement rates (LinkedIn ≥3%, Instagram ≥4%), and email list growth (500/month). Monthly reporting with quarterly strategy pivots.</div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- 1: SMART GOALS -->
<div class="section" id="s1">
  <div class="section-eyebrow"><div class="section-num">1</div><div class="section-label">Goal Setting</div></div>
  <h2>SMART Goals</h2>
  <p class="section-intro">Goals are set across all three business lines — Syndication/Investment, Brokerage, and CRE — ensuring each service area has measurable social media outcomes tied to real business growth.</p>
  <div class="smart-grid" style="margin-bottom:32px;">
    <div class="smart-cell"><div class="smart-letter">S</div><div class="smart-word">Specific</div><div class="smart-desc">Goals name an exact platform, metric, and outcome — never vague aims like "grow social media."</div></div>
    <div class="smart-cell"><div class="smart-letter">M</div><div class="smart-word">Measurable</div><div class="smart-desc">Each goal has a number trackable in platform analytics, UTM data, or CRM dashboards.</div></div>
    <div class="smart-cell"><div class="smart-letter">A</div><div class="smart-word">Achievable</div><div class="smart-desc">Targets are ambitious but calibrated to the brand's current content capacity and budget.</div></div>
    <div class="smart-cell"><div class="smart-letter">R</div><div class="smart-word">Relevant</div><div class="smart-desc">Every goal connects to investor acquisition, brokerage leads, CRE deals, or brand authority.</div></div>
    <div class="smart-cell"><div class="smart-letter">T</div><div class="smart-word">Time-bound</div><div class="smart-word" style="margin-top:4px;"></div><div class="smart-desc">Deadlines set at Months 3, 6, and 12 to create urgency and regular review checkpoints.</div></div>
  </div>
  <div class="grid-2">
    <div class="card card-gold"><div class="card-icon">📈</div><h3>Goal 1 — Audience Growth</h3><p>Grow combined following to <strong>10,000 engaged followers</strong> across LinkedIn, Instagram, and Facebook within 12 months, with 15% month-over-month growth rate in the first 6 months across all three business verticals.</p></div>
    <div class="card card-gold"><div class="card-icon">🎯</div><h3>Goal 2 — Investment Lead Generation</h3><p>Generate <strong>50 Investor Club sign-ups/month</strong> from social by Month 6 and <strong>30 discovery call bookings/month</strong> by Month 9, all tracked via UTM-tagged links from LinkedIn, Instagram, and paid campaigns.</p></div>
