  <p class="section-intro">A structured reporting cadence ensures data directly drives content and budget decisions across all three business lines. What gets measured gets improved — and what gets improved drives investor and client growth.</p>
  <div class="timeline" style="margin-bottom:36px;">
    <div class="timeline-item">
      <div class="timeline-phase">Weekly — Every Monday</div>
      <div class="timeline-title">Content Performance Check</div>
      <div class="timeline-desc">Review the top 3 and bottom 3 performing posts from the prior week across all business lines. Document what worked — topic, format, CTA, posting time. Track UTM-tagged link clicks separately for: Investor Club (syndication), brokerage inquiry form, and discovery call booking page. Adjust the coming week's content plan based on findings. Flag any listing inquiries from social that need same-day follow-up.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline-item">
      <div class="timeline-phase">Monthly — First Monday of Month</div>
      <div class="timeline-title">Full KPI Dashboard Review</div>
      <div class="timeline-desc">Pull all KPI data into a unified Sprout Social or Later dashboard. Review: follower growth vs. targets, engagement benchmarks per platform, conversion funnel performance per business line (syndication vs. brokerage vs. CRE inquiries), paid ad ROAS, and email list growth. Present a 1-page summary to Ankit and the team. Adjust next month's content calendar and ad budgets based on which business line is performing best.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline-item">
      <div class="timeline-phase">Quarterly — Every 3 Months</div>
      <div class="timeline-title">Strategy Pivot Review</div>
      <div class="timeline-desc">Full 90-day retrospective: Which platforms are driving the most leads per business line? Which content pillars are resonating — education, brokerage showcases, or CRE deal spotlights? Should budget be reallocated between business lines? Are personas still accurate? Review competitive landscape for new opportunities in syndication, brokerage, and CRE. Set revised targets and update all content calendars and paid campaign audiences.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline-item" style="margin-bottom:0;">
      <div class="timeline-phase">Annually — Year End</div>
      <div class="timeline-title">Full Roadmap Refresh</div>
      <div class="timeline-desc">Comprehensive Year 1 review vs. all SMART goals. Full competitive re-analysis across all three verticals. Platform algorithm changes and new feature review (e.g., LinkedIn's new ad formats, Instagram's shift in Reels algorithm). Update personas based on actual investor and client data from GoHighLevel CRM. Set Year 2 SMART goals with refined budget allocation per business line. Celebrate wins, document learnings, and rebuild the content calendar for Year 2.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="grid-2">
    <div class="card card-gold">
      <h3>12-Month Growth Milestones</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Month 1:</strong> All 5 platforms optimized, content system live, brokerage inquiry form linked in bios</li>
        <li><strong>Month 3:</strong> 1,000 followers, first 10 Investor Club sign-ups, first 5 brokerage inquiries from social</li>
        <li><strong>Month 6:</strong> 5,000 followers, 50 investor leads/month, 20 brokerage inquiries/month, YouTube at 500 subs</li>
        <li><strong>Month 9:</strong> 7,500 followers, 30 discovery calls/month, paid campaigns ROAS positive</li>
        <li><strong>Month 12:</strong> 10,000 followers, $1M+ in capital attributed to social, 20+ brokerage deals sourced from social media</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="card card-gold">
      <h3>Optimization Decision Tree</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Engagement below 2%?</strong> → Revisit hook strategy and test new content formats or topics</li>
        <li><strong>Brokerage inquiries flat?</strong> → Add stronger CTA to listing posts and run geo-targeted listing ads</li>
        <li><strong>Investor Club CTR low?</strong> → Audit link-in-bio page and simplify the sign-up process</li>
        <li><strong>CRE content underperforming?</strong> → Shift from data posts to deal story formats with real numbers</li>
        <li><strong>Paid ROAS below 2x?</strong> → Pause, refresh creative and ad copy, narrow audience targeting</li>
        <li><strong>One platform growing fastest?</strong> → Double content volume and budget there first</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
